Subject: SD3 conditioner: 1D pooled_g zero fallback when clip_g is missing

The sd::Tensor migration in upstream commit f16a110 ("refactor: migrate
generation pipeline to sd::Tensor") accidentally inflated the rank of the
zero fallback for missing clip_g pooled output:

  pre-refactor (faabc5ad):  ggml_new_tensor_1d(... 1280)        — rank 1
  post-refactor (f16a110):  sd::Tensor<float>::zeros({1280, 1}) — rank 2

The working path (real clip_g present) returns rank-1 pooled output of shape
[1280]. When clip_g is missing and clip_l is real, the subsequent
sd::ops::concat(pooled_l, pooled_g, 0) hits a rank mismatch:
"Tensor concat requires same rank: lhs_dim=1, rhs_dim=2".

This patch restores the original rank-1 fallback. Drop this file when
upstream merges the equivalent fix.

Tracking: <upstream issue/PR url here once filed>

diff --git a/src/conditioner.hpp b/src/conditioner.hpp
index 9f4d455..8309dc1 100644
--- a/src/conditioner.hpp
+++ b/src/conditioner.hpp
@@ -980,7 +980,7 @@ struct SD3CLIPEmbedder : public Conditioner {
             } else {
                 chunk_hidden_states_g = sd::Tensor<float>::zeros({1280, static_cast<int64_t>(chunk_len), 1});
                 if (chunk_idx == 0) {
-                    pooled_g = sd::Tensor<float>::zeros({1280, 1});
+                    pooled_g = sd::Tensor<float>::zeros({1280});
                 }
             }

